:: Malinche in Slavery [Done] {"position":"54,289","size":"100,100"}
Malinche, you will go down in history for living an extraordinary life, but historian Camilla Townsend has noted that your childhood was, in fact, quite ordinary. Your earliest years were marked by Nahua rituals, lessons, and roles assigned to you at birth. Even your sale into slavery was not uncommon, but is instead reflective of the social and political dynamics that defined your world. <br>
<br>
That story is one you know well, but it will be lost to future generations. Here is your chance to correct the historical record.<br>
<br>
A rumor has reached your village that a band of strange men have arrived upon the coast. Is this a chance to change your fortune? What might you tell these men about yourself that will work to your advantage? <br>

INSTRUCTIONS HERE FOR MALINCHE'S STORY TO BE WRITTEN ON GOOGLE SITES
<br>
Use what time you have to [[prepare your story|The Tabascans battle the Spaniards]].<br>


